org.apache.ctakes.ytex.kernel.evaluator

Class WeightedPolynomialMixingKernel

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.ctakes.ytex.kernel.evaluator.WeightedPolynomialMixingKernel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Kernel

    public class WeightedPolynomialMixingKernel
extends java.lang.Object
implements Kernel
    weighted polynomial mixing kernel: (\sum w_i * k(x_i, y_i) \div \sum w_i ) ^ l
    • Apply the delegate kernel to the respective 'parts' of this node (x_i, y_i)
    • Multiply the result by the weight (w_i * k(x_i,y_i))
    • Sum everything up, divide by the sum of the weights
    • take the power of everything to l
    pow the power to raise things to

    attributeKey the children of this node form a 'vector'. This is the attribute that we use to 'index' this vector

    mapIndexWeight the indices (i.e. the value of child.getValue().get(attributeKey) and the corresponding weights. The indices must be integers. The class must be identical to the class of the child - take care that the numeric types match.

    delegateKernel the kernel to apply to pairs of children.
